{{!--
    Labeled stat chip — small horizontal pill with an uppercase label and a
    bold numeric value, set against a translucent white card. Used by
    encumbrance and similar inventory readouts where multiple discrete
    "label : value" pairs sit side-by-side in a single panel body.

    Required hash params:
        label       — label text (already localized by caller).
        value       — value to display (already resolved by caller).

    Optional hash params:
        rootClass   — additional utility classes appended to the outer chip
                      (for layout positioning or override styling).
--}}
<div class="tw-flex tw-items-baseline tw-gap-2 tw-px-2 tw-py-1.5 tw-m-0.5 tw-bg-white/50 tw-rounded-md tw-border tw-border-black/10{{#if rootClass}} {{rootClass}}{{/if}}">
    <span class="tw-text-[0.85em] tw-font-semibold tw-uppercase tw-tracking-wide">{{label}}</span>
    <span class="tw-font-bold">{{value}}</span>
</div>
